- Thank you.
- Seriously.

1401
01:13:58,260 --> 01:13:59,470
Special guy.

1402
01:13:59,560 --> 01:14:01,560
Let me get the bed
comfortable for you, all right?

1403
01:14:03,020 --> 01:14:04,286
So are you gonna go out there now?

1404
01:14:04,310 --> 01:14:06,310
Yeah, I gotta figure my
plan out for tomorrow.

1405
01:14:06,400 --> 01:14:07,560
Why? Plan for what?

1406
01:14:07,650 --> 01:14:09,980
Well, I need to get
my head together.

1407
01:14:10,650 --> 01:14:12,070
How so?

1408
01:14:12,150 --> 01:14:15,410
This rich guy hit me up for a job. I
think I'm gonna get in touch with him.

1409
01:14:15,910 --> 01:14:17,990
- Really?
- Yeah.

1410
01:14:18,070 --> 01:14:20,830
- A job for what? What job?
- It doesn't matter. Just to get to Japan.

1411
01:14:21,160 --> 01:14:22,700
- For the championship?
- Yeah.

1412
01:14:23,200 --> 01:14:24,210
Wow.

1413
01:14:24,960 --> 01:14:28,040
Everything in my life is falling
apart, but I'm gonna figure it out.

1414
01:14:28,130 --> 01:14:29,840
Do you need any
help? I could help you.

1415
01:14:29,920 --> 01:14:31,816
- No, it's all right. It's all right.
- Can I do anything?

1416
01:14:31,840 --> 01:14:33,050
Are you hungry?

1417
01:14:33,130 --> 01:14:34,760
- No.
- You sure?

1418
01:14:34,840 --> 01:14:37,090
Uh, I'll just be in the
other room, all right?

1419
01:14:40,430 --> 01:14:42,866
- Dion, I've never seen anything like this.
- I told you, man.

1420
01:14:42,890 --> 01:14:44,290
Man, we have to have a big catch-up

1421
01:14:44,350 --> 01:14:47,326
'cause this is the greatest thing that's
happened to me in the last eight months.

1422
01:14:47,350 --> 01:14:48,860
Who would've thought? Halex?

1423
01:15:01,490 --> 01:15:03,240
<i>Good morning. Rockwell Ink.</i>

1424
01:15:03,330 --> 01:15:05,710
Yes, hi, can I speak to
Milton Rockwell, please?

1425
01:15:05,790 --> 01:15:07,790
<i>He's not in at the moment.
Can I take a message?</i>

1426
01:15:07,870 --> 01:15:09,146
Okay, when are you expecting him?

1427
01:15:09,170 --> 01:15:11,040
<i>Well, he's working off-site today.</i>

1428
01:15:11,130 --> 01:15:12,880
<i>- Again, can I take a message?</i>
- It's hot.

1429
01:15:12,960 --> 01:15:14,210
Thank you so much.

1430
01:15:14,300 --> 01:15:16,196
Can you make some for my
sister for when she wakes up?

1431
01:15:16,220 --> 01:15:17,720
- She'll be really hungry.
<i>- Hello?</i>

1432
01:15:17,800 --> 01:15:19,140
You said off-site where?

1433
01:15:19,220 --> 01:15:20,980
<i>I'm sorry, I can't give
you that information.</i>

1434
01:15:21,050 --> 01:15:22,946
<i>- Would you like to leave a message or not?</i>
- Yes.

1435
01:15:22,970 --> 01:15:25,390
Can you apologize
to him on my behalf?

1436
01:15:25,480 --> 01:15:27,456
I was the young gentleman that
was supposed to have breakfast

1437
01:15:27,480 --> 01:15:28,480
with him this morning.

1438
01:15:28,560 --> 01:15:30,860
<i>- I'm not familiar.
- From his son's battalion.</i>

1439
01:15:30,940 --> 01:15:33,730
<i>I'm sorry, I... I don't
know anything about that.</i>

1440
01:15:33,820 --> 01:15:36,716
<i>I have some personal belongings of
his son's I was supposed to give to him.</i>

1441
01:15:36,740 --> 01:15:39,740
<i>Letters and mementos and such,
but I messed up and I overslept.</i>

1442
01:15:39,820 --> 01:15:42,700
<i>I'm leaving town today, but I
could mail it to him if that's easier.</i>

1443
01:15:42,780 --> 01:15:44,790
<i>- No, no, no.
- No? Okay.</i>

1444
01:15:44,870 --> 01:15:49,040
<i>How about this, why don't you try
giving a call over to the Morosco Theatre.</i>

1445
01:15:49,540 --> 01:15:50,830
<i>The Morosco Theatre.</i>

1446
01:15:50,920 --> 01:15:53,420
So, I'm like what? What am I doing?

1447
01:15:53,500 --> 01:15:54,840
Coming up here to wreck my night.

1448
01:15:54,920 --> 01:15:56,776
Honest, Mama, I didn't even
know you were coming here.

1449
01:15:56,800 --> 01:15:58,026
I'm through with you playing games.

1450
01:15:58,050 --> 01:15:59,276
I was just coming for a good time.

1451
01:15:59,300 --> 01:16:01,680
I heard this was where
all the call girls gather.

1452
01:16:03,810 --> 01:16:07,520
I'm trying to rebuild my life
here. Don't you understand that?

1453
01:16:07,600 --> 01:16:09,770
More like selling out
to the highest bidder.

1454
01:16:09,850 --> 01:16:12,310
You've got no right
to judge me, Jed.

1455
01:16:12,400 --> 01:16:14,520
I fought tooth and nail for
every shred of happiness

1456
01:16:14,610 --> 01:16:17,166
- I've ever found while you...
- Right, and what did you give to me?

1457
01:16:17,190 --> 01:16:19,030
You never believed in me. Not once!

1458
01:16:20,240 --> 01:16:23,490
You wanna wallow in self-pity?
Well, here's an oven, Jed!

1459
01:16:23,580 --> 01:16:24,580
Alma!

1460
01:16:24,660 --> 01:16:25,660
I'm all right, Henry.

1461
01:16:25,740 --> 01:16:28,056
- Just give us a minute, please.
- My mama is a dirty bird.

1462
01:16:28,080 --> 01:16:29,960
Be careful now, Jedidiah.

1463
01:16:30,040 --> 01:16:34,420
And that fancy dress you put her in
is the only thing keeping in the stench!

1464
01:16:36,630 --> 01:16:38,800
Don't you lay a hand on my child.

1465
01:16:38,880 --> 01:16:40,590
I-I'm sorry, uh...

1466
01:16:45,310 --> 01:16:47,680
Mama, what did I do?

1467
01:16:47,770 --> 01:16:49,770
Go! Run!

1468
01:16:56,150 --> 01:16:58,740
- The door is locked.
- Oh, my God.

1469
01:16:58,820 --> 01:17:00,110
You've gotta be kidding me!

1470
01:17:00,190 --> 01:17:02,410
For Christ's sake, did
somebody put a latch on the door?

1471
01:17:02,490 --> 01:17:04,910
- Oh, God.
- I thought we had a good rhythm going.

1472
01:17:04,990 --> 01:17:08,200
A good rhythm going? On
what planet is that a good rhythm

1473
01:17:08,290 --> 01:17:09,676
- if you're alone in a room?
- I was in it.

1474
01:17:09,700 --> 01:17:12,290
It's like I wasn't even
there. In it? In what?

1475
01:17:12,370 --> 01:17:16,210
- Glenn, I couldn't get a word out.
- I understand. We're gonna fix it.

1476
01:17:16,290 --> 01:17:18,710
- That's what a rehearsal process is for.
- Fuck's sake.

1477
01:17:18,800 --> 01:17:20,800
Let's lose this, by the
way. Everybody take five.

1478
01:17:20,880 --> 01:17:22,220
Do me a favor, everybody...

1479
01:17:22,300 --> 01:17:24,510
Somebody needs
to tell him something.

1480
01:17:24,590 --> 01:17:26,390
- It's impossible.
- Impossible.

1481
01:17:27,930 --> 01:17:29,640
- Do you want some water?
- Yes.

1482
01:17:29,720 --> 01:17:31,890
- Let me bring you some.
- God.

1483
01:17:35,810 --> 01:17:37,230
Hey, Kay.

1484
01:17:37,320 --> 01:17:38,980
Hey, it's Marty.

1485
01:17:41,190 --> 01:17:42,990
From London.

1486
01:17:44,490 --> 01:17:45,490
What are you doing here?

1487
01:17:45,570 --> 01:17:47,306
Well, I got a friend in
the stagehands union.

1488
01:17:47,330 --> 01:17:48,556
I was dropping
something off for him.

1489
01:17:48,580 --> 01:17:50,660
- You watched that?
- Yeah, I hope that's okay.

1490
01:17:50,750 --> 01:17:51,790
Oh, God.

1491
01:17:51,870 --> 01:17:54,120
Hey, I can't believe
you're acting again.

1492
01:17:54,210 --> 01:17:56,290
That wasn't acting.
He won't let me act.

1493
01:17:56,380 --> 01:17:58,960
Yeah, no, that looked frustrating.
What's the deal with that guy?

1494
01:17:59,050 --> 01:18:00,300
Don't get me started.

1495
01:18:00,380 --> 01:18:02,090
Yeah, you were running
circles around him.

1496
01:18:02,880 --> 01:18:04,010
Of course I am.

1497
01:18:04,090 --> 01:18:05,640
Yeah. It was unbelievable.

1498
01:18:05,720 --> 01:18:07,300
He stays up for three days in a row

1499
01:18:07,390 --> 01:18:09,640
because his character
is supposed to be tired.

1500
01:18:09,720 --> 01:18:11,140
- It's obnoxious.
- Oh, God.

1501
01:18:12,810 --> 01:18:15,900
If he's so committed,
why'd he stop the scene?

1502
01:18:17,110 --> 01:18:18,956
Why didn't he punch his
hand through the screen,

1503
01:18:18,980 --> 01:18:20,180
unlock it from the other side?

1504
01:18:21,650 --> 01:18:23,416
- Right? That's what I would've done.
- Glenn!

1505
01:18:23,440 --> 01:18:24,950
- Yeah.
- Glenn!

1506
01:18:25,610 --> 01:18:27,620
- Yes. Thank you. Yes.
- I need to talk to you.

1507
01:18:30,160 --> 01:18:32,370
- Yes, what?
- What? What? What?

1508
01:18:32,450 --> 01:18:35,750
This kid understands the
character better than he does.

1509
01:18:35,830 --> 01:18:37,040
Excuse me?

1510
01:18:37,130 --> 01:18:38,686
- Tell him what you just told me.
- No, I don't want to.

1511
01:18:38,710 --> 01:18:39,710
No, tell him.

1512
01:18:39,790 --> 01:18:42,236
I was just saying you didn't really
seem like you were in the scene is all.

1513
01:18:42,260 --> 01:18:46,590
- Uh, who is this?
- He's nobody. That's the point.

1514
01:18:46,680 --> 01:18:51,510
Also, you know, in my experience,
only children hold a knife like this.

1515
01:18:51,600 --> 01:18:53,196
If it's a serious fight, you
hold your knife like this,

1516
01:18:53,220 --> 01:18:55,156
- with the blade square to your wrist.
- This is not a street fight.

1517
01:18:55,180 --> 01:18:56,746
Okay, well, if you're
not going for realistic,

1518
01:18:56,770 --> 01:18:58,250
you might as well
add a little flair.

1519
01:19:01,610 --> 01:19:02,690
Like that.

1520
01:19:02,780 --> 01:19:04,030
- Cut it out.
- Right, Kay?

1521
01:19:04,110 --> 01:19:07,030
Okay. Yeah, okay. Thanks for
the tutorial. Thank you very much.

1522
01:19:07,110 --> 01:19:10,780
Thank you very much indeed.
That's all we need today. Thank you.

1523
01:19:10,870 --> 01:19:12,596
- Best of luck, Kay. Best of luck.
- Get him out!

1524
01:19:12,620 --> 01:19:15,580
We no longer require your
presence. Thank you very much.

1525
01:19:15,660 --> 01:19:17,960
Well, with all due respect...

1526
01:19:18,040 --> 01:19:20,040
And yet every set
cost more than $5,000.

1527
01:19:20,130 --> 01:19:23,300
I can't just snap my fingers and get
your money and your wife into alignment.

1528
01:19:23,380 --> 01:19:24,920
I pay you to say no.

1529
01:19:25,010 --> 01:19:26,696
She seems to think
that this is carte blanche.

1530
01:19:26,720 --> 01:19:28,720
I can't just perform
the impossible here.

1531
01:19:28,800 --> 01:19:32,100
If you can't control her, I will
find someone else who can.

1532
01:19:32,180 --> 01:19:33,390
Asshole.

1533
01:19:38,100 --> 01:19:41,020
Mr. Rockwell. Mr. Rockwell.

1534
01:19:41,110 --> 01:19:43,650
- What?
- Hey. Marty Mauser. Nice to see you.

1535
01:19:43,730 --> 01:19:46,530
Did you call my office and
say you're friends with my son?

1536
01:19:47,610 --> 01:19:48,910
- Yes. But...
- Goddamn it!

1537
01:19:48,990 --> 01:19:51,030
I had no other way to get
in touch with you. Please.

1538
01:19:51,070 --> 01:19:52,676
I wanna revisit our
conversation about Japan.

1539
01:19:52,700 --> 01:19:54,926
I reconsidered it and I wanna
do it. I think it's a great idea.

1540
01:19:54,950 --> 01:19:56,846
The event's next week.
I've made alternate plans.

1541
01:19:56,870 --> 01:19:58,510
What other plans?
Okay, it was your idea.

1542
01:19:58,580 --> 01:20:01,606
It's a fantastic idea. Let's just have a
conversation about this for two seconds.

1543
01:20:01,630 --> 01:20:04,130
What are you doing?
Hey. Hey. Mr. Rockwell.

1544
01:20:04,210 --> 01:20:06,050
Please, let's both be
pragmatists about this.

1545
01:20:06,130 --> 01:20:08,276
Put your personal feelings
about me aside for a second.

1546
01:20:08,300 --> 01:20:11,300
You and I both know how much
value I would add with Endo.

1547
01:20:11,390 --> 01:20:13,180
In an exhibition on his home turf?

1548
01:20:13,260 --> 01:20:15,100
Imagine it. I'd be like
a stick of dynamite.

1549
01:20:15,180 --> 01:20:16,746
Whatever you have
planned, the alternative,

1550
01:20:16,770 --> 01:20:18,060
it's gonna pale in comparison.

1551
01:20:18,140 --> 01:20:19,270
Please give me two minutes.

1552
01:20:19,350 --> 01:20:22,440
We have enough common
ground to figure this out. Please!

1553
01:20:22,520 --> 01:20:24,900
- All right, get in the car.
- Really? Thank you.

1554
01:20:24,980 --> 01:20:26,190
Tommy, let's go.

1555
01:20:26,980 --> 01:20:29,200
Hey. Hey! Hey!

1556
01:20:29,280 --> 01:20:30,280
Hey!

1557
01:20:30,360 --> 01:20:32,660
You son of a bitch.
I gave you the idea!

1558
01:20:43,210 --> 01:20:45,840
I'm sorry. Miss Stone
wanted to let you know

1559
01:20:45,920 --> 01:20:47,670
that she'd love to
have lunch with you.

1560
01:20:47,760 --> 01:20:49,340
- Miss Stone?
- Yes.

1561
01:21:06,110 --> 01:21:07,530
<i>My God, I'm so late.</i>

1562
01:21:07,610 --> 01:21:09,110
<i>Come on. What do you care?</i>

1563
01:21:09,190 --> 01:21:11,650
<i>You're the star. Gotta
feel pretty good, right?</i>

1564
01:21:11,740 --> 01:21:13,580
<i>I mean, why'd you even
stop in the first place?</i>

1565
01:21:13,610 --> 01:21:16,200
I wanted security,
and I got pregnant,

1566
01:21:17,120 --> 01:21:19,830
and he pressured me, and I settled.

1567
01:21:19,910 --> 01:21:22,290
Well, I mean, clearly, you're
doing the right thing now

1568
01:21:22,370 --> 01:21:24,500
and it sounds like he's
paying you back with interest.

1569
01:21:24,580 --> 01:21:26,710
- Who is?
- Your husband.

1570
01:21:26,790 --> 01:21:28,396
I mean, he's funding
your whole show, right?

1571
01:21:28,420 --> 01:21:29,260
Where'd you get that idea?

1572
01:21:29,340 --> 01:21:30,986
I overheard him complaining
about it in the lobby.

1573
01:21:31,010 --> 01:21:32,840
- Complaining?
- Yeah, about the costs.

1574
01:21:34,010 --> 01:21:35,470
He can go fuck himself.

1575
01:21:35,550 --> 01:21:37,150
Completely. You know
what you should do,

1576
01:21:37,180 --> 01:21:39,060
you should leech him for
every penny he's worth,

1577
01:21:39,100 --> 01:21:40,866
assume your place as the
biggest star on the planet,

1578
01:21:40,890 --> 01:21:42,690
and then you rub it
in his smug little face.

1579
01:21:42,770 --> 01:21:45,810
Thank you, but I'm really not
looking for life advice from you.

1580
01:21:45,900 --> 01:21:48,900
No, I'm just saying you clearly
never needed him in the first place.

1581
01:21:50,440 --> 01:21:52,530
Like with me, I'm never
accepting anyone's help.

1582
01:21:52,610 --> 01:21:56,660
I gotta do it completely on my own.
Purely on the basis of my own talent.

1583
01:21:56,740 --> 01:21:59,830
Otherwise it's, like, the
success won't even count.

1584
01:21:59,910 --> 01:22:01,040
But that's just me.

1585
01:22:01,120 --> 01:22:03,330
Yes, well, that's very easy to say.

1586
01:22:03,410 --> 01:22:06,210
Well, it's easy to say but
it's sure not easy to do.

1587
01:22:06,290 --> 01:22:08,500
I mean, you know that.
That's why you cashed out.

1588
01:22:11,050 --> 01:22:12,380
Let me ask you something.

1589
01:22:13,050 --> 01:22:15,430
Do you make money at
this little table tennis thing?

1590
01:22:15,510 --> 01:22:17,760
- Not yet.
- Do you have a job?

1591
01:22:18,350 --> 01:22:20,430
No. I mean, table tennis is my job.

1592
01:22:20,510 --> 01:22:21,520
How do you live?

1593
01:22:21,600 --> 01:22:22,640
I live with the confidence

1594
01:22:22,680 --> 01:22:24,456
that if I believe in myself,
the money will follow.

1595
01:22:24,480 --> 01:22:26,940
Ultimately, my struggle
isn't even about money.

1596
01:22:27,020 --> 01:22:29,110
- How do you pay rent?
- I don't.

1597
01:22:29,190 --> 01:22:31,336
- You're avoiding the question.
- No, I'm not avoiding anything.

1598
01:22:31,360 --> 01:22:33,070
How do you plan
on eating food today?

1599
01:22:33,150 --> 01:22:36,490
Honestly, I was gonna order
room service the second you leave.

1600
01:22:36,570 --> 01:22:38,990
- Nice.
- Yeah. Nice.

1601
01:22:39,080 --> 01:22:42,160
And what do you plan to do if this
whole dream of yours doesn't work out?

1602
01:22:42,240 --> 01:22:44,330
That doesn't even
enter my consciousness.

1603
01:22:44,410 --> 01:22:46,250
Okay. Well, maybe it should.

1604
01:22:47,210 --> 01:22:48,210
Wow.

1605
01:22:48,750 --> 01:22:51,460
You sound like my mom. No offense.

1606
01:22:51,550 --> 01:22:53,300
And you sound like a child.

1607
01:22:53,380 --> 01:22:55,550
Oh, yeah? Clearly I'm old enough.

1608
01:22:55,630 --> 01:22:56,986
And what is that supposed to mean?

1609
01:22:57,010 --> 01:22:58,656
That I'm old enough to
fuck you in your hotel room

1610
01:22:58,680 --> 01:23:00,470
in the middle of your big comeback.

1611
01:23:00,550 --> 01:23:01,680
You're disgusting.

1612
01:23:04,060 --> 01:23:05,060
Break a leg.

1613
01:23:12,820 --> 01:23:14,530
No, I know, but I was out of town

1614
01:23:14,610 --> 01:23:16,950
so I only just received it
yesterday for the first time.

1615
01:23:17,490 --> 01:23:20,320
Well, look, not coming
to Japan is not an option.

1616
01:23:20,950 --> 01:23:24,080
Okay, well, just let Mr. Sethi know
that a cashier's check in the full amount

1617
01:23:24,160 --> 01:23:26,000
is already on the way
to him. It's in the mail.

1618
01:23:26,620 --> 01:23:27,726
No, that's fine, but just...

1619
01:23:27,750 --> 01:23:29,670
I don't want any confusion
about my attendance.

1620
01:23:29,750 --> 01:23:31,766
I'm gonna be there. I'm gonna be
there when the tournament starts.

1621
01:23:31,790 --> 01:23:35,170
- I got it!
- Yes! Yes! Yes!

1622
01:23:36,130 --> 01:23:37,130
How much do you think?

1623
01:23:38,680 --> 01:23:40,276
- This is not real.
- What do you mean it's not real?

1624
01:23:40,300 --> 01:23:42,460
- Total fake.
- It came from the neck of a millionaire.

1625
01:23:42,510 --> 01:23:43,850
I saw it come off her neck.

1626
01:23:43,930 --> 01:23:47,890
I don't care where it came
from. It's total garbage.

1627
01:23:47,980 --> 01:23:49,810
- Costume jewelry.
- Costume jewelry?

1628
